<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Belgrade</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-10"><hi rend="italic">July 10,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 78. Servian series.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report the receipt
                            to-day of a note from Mr. Zujovic, the Servian minister of foreign
                            affairs, requesting the transmission to my government of the expression
                            of the sincere regrets of the Royal Servian Government at the loss
                            suffered by the people of the United States in the person of that very
                            distinguished citizen and eminent statesman Hon. John Hay.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Jackson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>